Suppose the following conditions hold.
\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{(Law class.)} The observed law \(P\) belongs to the class \(\mathcal P(\alpha,\gamma)\) of Definition~\ref{obj:def:law-class}.
\item \textbf{(Sampling.)} The observations \(O_i=(X_i,A_i,Y_i)\) satisfy Assumption~\ref{obj:ass:iid}.
\item \textbf{(Policy and oracle.)} The policy class satisfies Assumption~\ref{obj:ass:policy-class}, and the oracle policy is in the class as required by Assumption~\ref{obj:ass:optimal-in-class}.
\item \textbf{(Cross-fitting and nuisances.)} The fixed fold count condition of Assumption~\ref{obj:ass:fixed-crossfit-fold-count}, the nuisance-rate condition of Assumption~\ref{obj:ass:nuisance-rate}, the bounded cross-fitted nuisance condition of Assumption~\ref{obj:ass:bounded-crossfit-nuisances}, and the polynomial nuisance-rate exponents of Assumption~\ref{obj:ass:polynomial-nuisance-exponents} hold.
\item \textbf{(ERM and empirical-process control.)} Let \(\widehat\pi_n\) be the clipped-AIPW \(1/n\)-ERM of Definition~\ref{obj:def:feasible-erm}; use the feasible-ERM basic inequality of Lemma~\ref{obj:lem:feasible-erm-basic-inequality}, the clipped-score drift identity of Lemma~\ref{obj:lem:clip-bias}, the cross-fit localized offset control of Lemma~\ref{obj:lem:crossfit-localized-offset-control}, and the localized VC self-bound of Lemma~\ref{obj:lem:localized-vc-self-bound}.
\end{itemize}

Then the regret \(R_P(\widehat\pi_n)\) of Definition~\ref{obj:def:welfare-regret} satisfies the following bounds. If \(\gamma>0\) and \(q\le c_o u^\gamma\), then, for a finite constant \(C\),
\[
\mathbb E_P R_P(\widehat\pi_n)
\le
C\left\{
n^{-r_\star(\alpha,\gamma)}
+(nq^2)^{-A_\alpha}
+\frac{r_{\mu,n}r_{e,n}}{q}
+r_{\mu,n}u^{\alpha/2}q^{1/(2\gamma)}
+\frac{r_{\mu,n}^2}{u}
\right\}(\log n)^p .
\]
If \(\gamma=0\) and \(q\le \underline p/2\) is fixed, then
\[
\mathbb E_P R_P(\widehat\pi_n)
\le
C\left\{
n^{-A_\alpha}
+r_{\mu,n}r_{e,n}
\right\}(\log n)^p .
\]
